Ursicinus of Saint-Ursanne - Wikipedia Ursicinus of Saint-Ursanne From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia Jump to navigation Jump to search Saint Ursicinus of Saint-Ursanne Statue of St. Ursicinus, Hermitage St-Ursanne Died c. 620 AD Venerated in Roman Catholic Church Orthodox Church Major shrine Saint-Ursanne; venerated at Basel , Besançon , and Mainz Feast December 20 Attributes abbot with three lilies in his hand or holding a book and fleur-de-lys , surrounded by fleur-de-lys Patronage invoked against stiff neck Saint Ursicinus (also Hursannus, Ursitz, Oschanne , fl. 620) was an Irish missionary and hermit in the Jura region . Contents 1 Information 2 References 3 Notes 4 External links Information [ edit ] A vita of his is preserved in a redaction of the 11th century. According to this account, he was a disciple of Saint Columbanus at Luxeuil who followed his master when he was banished from Burgundy in 610, but then retired as a hermit in the Doubs valley . Veneration of Ursicinus is attested since the 7th century.
In Grandval , a church was dedicated to Ursicinus in 675. By the 11th century, he was part of the local canon of saints of the Besançon diocese. His feast day is on 20 December. Ursicinus' supposed sarcophagus is preserved in St-Ursanne in what is now the canton of Jura in Switzerland . References [ edit ] Wikimedia Commons has media related to Category:Saint Ursicinus . Notes [ edit ] Andreas Merkt, Ursicinus in Biographisch-Bibliographisches Kirchenlexikon , vol. 12 (1997). External links [ edit ] Catholic Online: Ursicinus of Saint-Ursanne Saint of the Day, December 20: Ursicinus of Saint-Ursanne (in Italian) Sant' Ursicino del Giura Authority control HDS : 010208 This article about an Irish saint is a stub . You can help Wikipedia by expanding it . v t e This Swiss biographical article is a stub . You can help Wikipedia by expanding it . v t e Retrieved from " https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Ursicinus_of_Saint-Ursanne&oldid=970634190 " Categories : 7th-century Irish people 7th-century Christian saints Swiss Roman Catholic saints Canton of Jura 625 deaths Medieval Irish saints on the Continent Colombanian saints Irish Roman Catholic saint stubs Swiss people stubs Hidden categories: Articles with Italian-language sources (it) Wikipedia articles with HDS identifiers Year of birth unknown All stub articles Navigation menu Personal tools Not logged in Talk Contributions Create account Log in Namespaces Article Talk Variants Views Read Edit View history More Search Navigation Main page Contents Current events Random article About Wikipedia Contact us Donate Wikipedia store Contribute Help Community portal Recent changes Upload file Tools What links here Related changes Upload file Special pages Permanent link Page information Cite this page Wikidata item Print/export Download as PDF Printable version In other projects Wikimedia Commons Languages Deutsch Français Hrvatski Italiano Edit links This page was last edited on 1 August 2020, at 14:01 (UTC) . Text i